The General Inquirer

This Spiral No
tebook is an attempt to recapitulate and interpret a once widely used text
irst developed in the 1960s by Philip Stone and colleagues. One of the innovatio
ns of the General Inquirer was its use of a dictionary to map keywords onto diff
erent cateories. Among other things, this allows us to search for instances of e
ach keyword in a text and to measure the relative preponderance of a category.</
